<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="585" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d585">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/265</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 12, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Manati Sugar Company, 110 Wall Street, New York, states impossible to
                            communicate with their properties at Manati. Fear destruction of
                            property and interference with operation and that they are receiving no
                            protection from Cuban Government. Bring urgently attention of President
                            Menocal and request protection for this property.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>